\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What year were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 19 - 8 - 1900.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What year were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 18 - 1877.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Westwood in Nottinghamshire
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you remember how long you lived in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well my mother told me we were only there one year after I was born and then we removed to Fletcher's Row at Codnor Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That was another village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. About three miles from the other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, we was only there about two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And where did you move to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We moved to Riddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And how long were you at Riddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I - I was there 'til 1905.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You were there until you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And you lived in Riddings for five years after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That was it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When you were a child you made the different moves first of all from Westwood when you were about a year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And then to Codnor Park - can you remember why the family moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well it was to be a little bit nearer me father's work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It wasn't to move to a bigger house or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. No. It was to be nearer his work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Three brothers and two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you tell me the order in which they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, the first brother - the - the - I haven't got his name - the first brother was born in '75.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 1875?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
And the next brother was born in 1876. I was born in 18 - in 1877. And then sister and - was born in '79 - 1879. Then there was another brother born but I don't know the year it was 'cos he was still born. And then my other sister was born in 7 - in 1883.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did all your brothers and sisters live for a long time or did any of them die when they were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well me first brother was a year and ten months old when he died. And the next brother was two months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So that your mother's first two children both died very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you tell me how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Twenty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Chesterfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, as a boy he was a - what they called a hanger-on at a colliery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old would he be then do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He started when he was nine years old. Then he left that and went to work in the ironstone mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you know how old he was when he went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - well, I - I - I don't think they let them go in 'til they was about twelve - I think he'd be about - yes. Then his parents left Chesterfield. And came to Pye Hill - at Codnor Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And what job did he do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Went to the stone mines went to work in the stone - ironstone mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The same one or a different one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It wasn't the same as he'd worked at Chesterfield but it was the same kind of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long did he carry on doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Right 'til the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 stone mines}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  closed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 About how old would he be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well it - he - they closed when he'd be about twenty I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What job did he take up then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Coal mining.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he do that for the rest of the working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He didn't have any other job at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not 'til - no, not from then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he have any casual jobs or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Or on strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He was on strike in the 1893 strike - sixteen weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That would affect your standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, it did - yes, it did. Of course there was no strike pay only for two weeks and that was only eight shillings each week. And - what lit
tle money they'd saved you see they had to - get it and they came round bringing bread and different things round the village and tea and there was - soup kitchens opened out and different things like that right }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  it - the strike was over. And when the 
strike was finished the manager at the colliery - that owned the colliery he had several sheep killed and each miners wife had to go and they gave 'em a piece of mutton for the family. According - according to the family. So that the men should have a hot
 meal the day they came home from work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Twenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Codnor Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she go out to work before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she have any job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
No, no, they had a large - she was the oldest in the family. She had to help to do the work and look after the children. And mother was not a very strong woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 She didn't have a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you remember anything else about your parents lives or your grandparents or people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, when I was young my father - my great grandfather was living. My father's grandfather and he died when he was eighty-si
x. I was ten years old. I remember him very well - he was a very big man - bonny man and when he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 ninety}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 years of age he took me to the Rugby Fair. He came - he lived at Derby but his daughter - my grandmother - lived at Ripley and they always came ever
y fair. And when he was ninety he took me up to the fair among the horses and carts with no-one but just us two.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old did you say he was when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Ninety-six. No, ninety-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He looked after you then and took you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes. To the fair - yes. I was young you see. I should be about six years old. And my - grandfather and grandmother they were - they lived to be - one was eighty odd and the other was seventy odd when they died. My father's mother an
d father but my mother - my mother's father he lived to be seventy-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So the eldest relative you can remember was your great-grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And he was ninety-six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Ninety-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So when would he be born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When would he be born? Well, in 17 - 1791 about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That\rquote s going back a fair way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many rooms were there in the house at Riddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Two up and two down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Any outhouses or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Any what? No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did anybody else besides you and your mother and father and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You wouldn't have room would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. 'Cos we'd only a living room one was - with a - fire range in the - we did the cooking then 
what we called the back kitchen there was a fireplace in but there was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 sink stone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 - and the water. Well you - we hadn't water at first when we lived not in the house - we had to fetch it from a - a pump about twenty yards away and then there, was water - they put a water main in the village and we had water in the house then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother pay anybody to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 She did all the work herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. And in them days the co
pper that you boiled your clothes in it was outside. And you had to make the fire and get the hot water out of doors. It wasn't in the house and boil it - and if it was a wet day it was - very awkward.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother make the fire for the copper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Or did your father help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, he'd be gone to work 'cos he went at - he started from home at five o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother or father make or mend any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, my mother mended and ma
de all our clothes - underclothes and dresses. She had a machine - we had a machine and she used to do all like that. And me father would mend our shoes - bobble them - but he didn't do any other sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So all your clothes were made rather than bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Oh yes, we never - we never bought any ready made - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, shoes weren't as dear as they are these days - that we had new shoes. And then me father mended them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And they were new shoes that you bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You never bought any secondhand clothes or shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your father do anything at all in the house - cleaning or cooking or repairs, handyman jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, he didn't do any cleaning or cooking but he would do litt
le bits of things if we was - beautifying he would help with that - when he wasn't at work but you see he went to work at - he left house at five o'clock in the morning and he wasn't home again 'til four - half past in the afternoon. Well he was tired the
n you see. It took him all his time to do the garden - what bit of garden we had then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So that he never did anything in the house really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he do anything for you as children - did he dress you or undress you or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
No, he couldn't - no, he didn't read to us - no. 'Cos he hadn't had a good education and he couldn't - he could read but not read out aloud. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Had he been to school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no
t - no. My mother - she'd only been school very lit - little. Not much. She could just read and write and she learnt him to read and write after they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 . He was anxious to do that - and he was very determined that we children should have the best
 education that we could have. For he said it had been bad for him with not being educated. He lost quite a number of jobs that he could have had if he'd have been educated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would he take you out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, he'd take us out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh yes, he'd take us - perhaps to Ripley to see a - grandparents without me mother or anything. Yes, he'd take us out. But very often at the weekend all of us used to go over to the grandparents at Ripley - to the market and then to Ripley to see them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, he would do if she was out - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever have any tasks to carry out at home to help your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not really. Perhaps sometimes help to wipe the dishes or something like that but we hadn't really anything set to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't look after the younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh well, yes, when you was out at play we had to look after them. 'Cos I was the oldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have to do anything towards helping them to dress themselves or anything like that or did your mother do it all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - me mother would dress the youngest but the - the one that was next to me I'd help her perhaps to dress a bit sometimes but - that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did any of your brothers and sisters have to do anything in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It would be your sisters wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, sisters - yes. No, me being the oldest if anything had to be done it was me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well we didn't have a real set time but we were never up - after eight o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother or anybody else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, when we - 'til we'd be about nine or ten she did and then we would go ourselves up to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 With me sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the sleeping arrangements of the family - there'd be your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In one - the front room. And then my two sisters and me in the other one. We had a full size bed and a single one in the other room.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We - in the - in the soul - back kitchen downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Now often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh every week at least. On - if they got dirty they were bathed before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh every week. We never missed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That's underclothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about top clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, pinafores clean every day. We wore pinafores in them days. 'Course they didn't wash fro
cks like they do now, they were dark. They were washed occasionally but not very often. But the skirts and other things were all washed every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did the family have meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In the front - in the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any occasions when you ate in a different room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - perhaps if we'd company - sometimes when we had company there wasn't room for us all to sit at table in the front room and mother would put a table in the kitchen and we would have - children have our meal th
ere at the same time as they were having theirs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In this - living room or front room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And it was a fire cooking range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 There was just a oven at the side and a boiler that had got water in. It isn't like a c
ooking range like they are now it's just-was just a fire - oven at one side and a - a boiler at the other that you put hot water in that was where we had the only hot water we had - only what we boiled in the copper outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When was? Oh, about eight 'o'clock or just gone eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Which members of the family were present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 My two sisters and mother. And father had had his at - before five o'clock - before he went to work you see by himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He got up and saw himself off to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you usually eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, bread and butter or something like that. Or bread and jam - we didn't have any cooked breakfast. Before we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, we had a drink of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have anything different on special days such as Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh well, Sundays we - for breakfast we would generally have a bit of bacon or perhaps an egg or something like that at Sunday 
when we were all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you have for your mid-day meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, we didn't have our dinner 'til night - 'til my father came home from work but at mid-day my mother would give us the - any cold things that was left over the day before or we'd have perhaps bread and cheese or a boiled egg - anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you call your mid-day meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We - I don't know. We'd say we'd come home for the dinner, you see, from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You called it dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What was your next meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, it would be that - five o'clock when my father was home and we would have - vegetables and meat and pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And what to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any different pattern from this on Sundays? Did you have a cooked meal at mid-day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes, we had it at dinner time at Sunday. And - we had tea at tea time - a cake or - bread and jam or anything. Generally cake and something like that for tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That was your Sunday tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have cake any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So that it wasn't anything really special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, sometimes - might - we had a jelly perhaps and sometimes on a Sunday - or a blancmange my mother would make but - nothing - or it was stewed fruit sometimes and we would have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You wouldn't have these things on other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, occasionally we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. And cakes - everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Oh, anything like that. And pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, she did make wine with redcurrants out of the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about medicine - did she concoct any medicines for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Herbs - yes. She used to give us herb teas to drink. If we weren't well we had a - she 
had a patch about three yards square and it was full of herbs - all kinds and we'd have root tea or oran tea if we weren't well. Just what they thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, in summer we brewed herb beer with these herbs out of the garden.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It sounds as if you had quite a big garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well it wasn't ever so big not really, but it - there was fruit trees all round it and we had three - three apple trees and a large bed of rhubarb that we - we hadn't much room to grow very many vegetables. Gooseberry bushes we had - and fruit really.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't grow enough to keep you going on your own produce all the year - you used to have to buy some things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. Oh yes, we did for - for a good number of years until my fat
her got an allotment. They were - then we grew potatoes and more vegetables then - after we had this allotment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When did he get the allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, that's - I should think - I should be about fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Before you got the allotment they used to buy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Had to buy vegetables - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were they always fresh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, there was fresh fruit - fresh vegetables. You get them from the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But after you had the allotment you were able to grow enough for all your needs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - nearly all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What were you not able to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It used to be the green ones that we - enough potatoes always but such things as beans and peas like that had to - we'd grow some but w
e wasn't able to, you know, to last you through the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you sell any of the produce at all or did you use it all yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh we used it all ourselves then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They didn't keep any livestock did they - hens, pigs, goats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well we had - we had about six hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So you had some of your own eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who looked after the hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well my mother's just feed them and we children went to buy the corn for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How far did you have to go for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 About a mile and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How much did you bring at a time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We'd bring - half a stone - seven pounds. Of Indian corn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You'd have to buy some eggs as well would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, we had to buy some in between - yes. But - we did have a few from them yo
u see while they was laying. 'Course they'd go off laying some part of the year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 While they were laying they produced enough for the family's needs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Just then - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh most days we had a bit of meat. Meat - beef, liver and different things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 This would be fresh meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You never had any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit as the result of somebody poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No
 - we didn't get it - we did buy rabbits but not from poachers - the green - the fishmonger sold rabbits. We could get one for about ninepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't know any poachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember seeing your mother ever have less food so that the rest of the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no, I never saw having -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well he - he did - he was - he was a bigger eater than we were but we'd always sufficient. I mean if we wanted more we asked for more you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Even during the strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well during the strike we seemed to get sufficient for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well we could - we could just talk to - didn't do a lot of talking I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You concentrated on the eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Eating - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well we generally had a bit of everything. But you could - if it was something we didn't like me mother wouldn'
t give it us but as a rule we liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I don't remember us ever leaving very much. We - they didn't give us so much at once and then we asked for a second lot you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 If there was something on the table that you wanted such as the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Or did you have to wait }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. You could ask for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Or sit in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well we had to - we'd have had to hold it in a proper manner. We was told if we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about sitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh we had to sit up straight. To the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Could you bring toys or a book to the table at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
When - we - when you'd finished your meal that you - if you wanted to leave you said please can I leave the table and you was allowed to leave it. You didn't jump up when you'd eat it and go away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did all the family sit at the table for their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How was the meal served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 By whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 My - my mother would bring the vegetable dishes on the table and the meat and she'd always carve the meat. The she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 She would serve the vegetables to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, my - my mother generally served my father first and then us children after. And herself the last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did the younger sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well the family had a high chair and they sat in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - me - both mother and father'd feed them a bit. My father would feed us. Seen him feeding a baby many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When were the younger ones able to join the family for meals - how old would they be when they came up to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I should say - about two years old - as soon as they could sit nice to the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You felt quite close to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Could you share any worries with her if you had any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, you - you could - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was your father easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He was about the same - yes, quite easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you confide any worries in him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, you could do if you wanted - if you had any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, properly - in a proper manner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you be more specific than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well now - I - I don't know quite how to say - I'm sure -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents bring }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 you up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, yes, to be kind to them and - and such. And look after them. See they didn't get into any danger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they say that you should hit back or not if another child hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It depended. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 
If it was a bigger one than you, you couldn't hit them back but they didn't say - they didn't interfere with us in that way.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They left you to sort your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd be when you grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, respectable and honest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they bring you up to consider that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes. We had to be honest and truthful and such things as that you know. And do a good turn to anyone if you could. Anything like that. Help anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh - we dread - we ne
ver hear any bad language in our house. We were not allowed to go where any was. If my parents found out that children outside were swearing they wouldn't allow us to go - mix with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When the grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well it depended on the conversations. What it was about and such things. We could - we could join in different things but it just depended on the conversation what they were talking about you see. If it was something we didn't understand we weren't all
owed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen - would you be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - we - we would in a way. We should get a very good reprimanding. Make us feel ashamed of ourselves you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would this be from your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, either of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really. Only for slight things - no, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You weren't punished very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh disgraced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one of them play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 For our behaviour do you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 mean?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  Well, no they - both parents - I mean we really had - we behaved to you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, sometimes we'd have a birthday cake - my mother'd bake us a birthday cake and something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Occasionally from our aunts like we'd get a few coppers perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Anything from your mother and father or your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No not - not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And you sometimes had a cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever have a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh we have had - we did have parties sometimes but not every birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was this true in each case of the three children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was it what? Yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The younger ones didn't have any special privileges that you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you remember anything you with your mother and father together oh Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We play - we had - played games sometimes and they generally on Christmas took us to our grandparents - either my mother's or my father
's people. We generally went the Christmas day - day - for tea - not for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not - not until I was - I should say twenty-one. Then we had a piano. But not before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was that in your parents home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who played it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, my younger sister did a bit of - she played it a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did anybody in the family sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 My young sister. She was a very good singer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would you like to tell me a bit about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, as 
a child they called on her for most of the concerts. She once played in - at a operetta called Red Riding Hood and - different things like that. And she went to the choral society - which I - I went as well. And she would sing the choruses like in the Mes
siah what the soprano would sing for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 choir.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  Then the choir would sing the chorus and she would do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 She'd sing the solo parts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, in the practices not the concert - in the practices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What choral society was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was called the Reddings Choral Society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It was something for the whole village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It wasn't from a particular church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, no it - it was - it was the whole village - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever make music at home together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well -
 we - before we had the piano we would sing - my father and mother were very fond of singing. My mother wasn't a bad singer and we all used to do a lot - we used to do a lot of singing and father was very fond of singing. And as children he used to start 
us singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of songs did you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh - all the songs that were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 going about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  you know. I can't tell you exactly the names of them now. But all the - all the popular songs that were about. They would sing them and we children would learn them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. We - we'd play - snakes and ladders or dominoes and different things like that they'd play with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about outdoor games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh well, play at ball sometimes and on the back but we didn't play in the street with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents join in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They would do - me father would play ball with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Any particular ball game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, not particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of books - can you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well children story books and story books that we got from the - Chapel Library when I was a bit older such as - well, I can't tell you - I can't remember the names exactly - but there was always story books you know. There 
wasn't a proper library in the village but this one chap had a very small library and it used to let you have a - have a book out and like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was that free of charge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you take newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you remember what newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Nottingham Evening Post.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The Umpire we took that in sometime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was that a daily newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, weekly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What kind of a newspaper was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well it was full of - I can't tell you exactly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was it local?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, no not all - exactly local. It was - took Nottinghamshire and that in you know like. Not just Riddings it was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It was a provincial newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. And then we had - oh, the Alfreton times, we took that in. That was a weekly paper. That was more - local news.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't have a daily paper apart from the Nottingham Evening Post?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The church magazine that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They used to read the newspaper and the magazine - church magazine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they read any books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I never remember them reading books - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they ever what? Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 my own}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  home. But I remember my aunt's children dying and things like that. And of course I remember my grandmother dying but I was eighteen then when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was her death and funeral the one that you would remember best then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - I remember me grandmother very well - her dying. 'Cos of course I was eighteen then and - my aunt's two young children died - I'd be sixteen I think when they died. They lived very near to us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who attended you grandmother's funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, me mother and father and they had brothers and sisters and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We didn't go to the funeral - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They would wear mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes, yes. Black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Could you tell me what the custom was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, the custom was for them to wear black and all the ladies wore black veils for the funeral and - for those that carried the corpse they was generally - white and wore white gloves for a baby - see if it was a baby. And the
re was generally young women carried them - there were no coaches like that - no biers like there is today, not in Riddings. They was all carried. And - and young women had them, and there was like a big white }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 sheet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - well, almost like a sheet rolled up you see and then you - you carried the baby like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about an adult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 adult}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - was generally men that carried them and they carried them shoulder high but they had to go a long way. It would be - over two miles. I remember - I have se
veral times carried babies that have died for different people. And carried babies for several different people quite the - used to come when you did - when you went - didn't belong to them at all. Come and ask you to go - to carry the babies to the funer
al you see. Oh yes. Any young woman that had a black -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Any person that had a black dress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, a young woman - they would come from all over the village for you to go to the - carry the babies to the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you do this often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Wel
l, perhaps two or three times in a year. They'd come round and ask you, you see, to go. 'Course sometimes it wasn't convenient for you to go and you'd - you'd refuse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 With our parents. Yes, some - we were often taken to aunts and grandmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did anybody else ever take you visiting people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, not really - my aunts - perhaps aunts who lived in the village - there was had two that lived in the village - they would take you s
ometimes with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were you taken shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - wasn't very many shops and we were sent to the Co-operative shopping and - instead of my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you do it often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, perhaps once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't go shopping with your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, yes, if - sometimes we would or sometimes she'd leave us out playing while she went. It wasn't very far to the shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Sometimes. He'd take us for a walk sometimes, you 
know, like that. Up and down the fields or the - take us to his mothers and different things I mean. Me mother didn't always go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, for instance, on Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, they didn't seem to - we didn't do much on - only to - but not going out anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - it didn't seem very much different only we would go with the parents to Riple
y to that - to the market and then call and see me grandmother - some - we did sometimes at Saturdays. Sometimes one - grandmother and sometimes another. But we didn't seem to do anything different than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, we didn't often go out anywhere at Sundays only we went to Sunday school, you see. Chapel at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 morning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  and night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Methodist that was - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have different clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you wear these clothes all day after you'd been to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, all day Sunday. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 
Always had different clothes and different shoes on Sunday.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you play games at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not really much - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents think that it was wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, I don't think they did really but you see we went to Sunday school and we'd no time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. They didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. Not then. No. But when I was a -
 about twelve or thirteen my father joined the Christadelphians and he used to go on Sunday afternoons to Swanwick to the - a meeting there, but that was all that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You went to Sunday school Sunday afternoons?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any Sunday school outings organised from time to time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well we had a Band of Hope belonging the Sunday school and we used to pay a penny a month and then I remember only - well, twice - they took us to the seaside. The first time I ever saw the sea and i
t was at Skegness. We'd saved a shilling in the Band of Hope and that took us to there and we had to take our own food and I remember my mother gave us sixpence to spend and the food and - at Skegness there was a - we were provided with a bun and a mug of
 tea from the Band of Hope. That was first time I ever went to the sea. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old would you be then - can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Why I should think ten at least.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was that really the first outing you'd ever been on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. That was. That 
- yes. Then in - the - two years after we had another Band of Hope party and we went to Mablethorpe and it was similar to that one, see. We saved - we'd saved the money - but that was one - it cost one and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That was for the fare?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. And we had sixpence to spend and we thought that was a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you spend your sixpence on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - we had sweets and I think a bit of food of some kind, in the - and then we bought some little present or - my sister and I together - put together and bought a cup and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 saucer}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  and it said a present from Skegness on it. Cost sixpence - that took threepence from each of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What else did you do while you were at Skegness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, only play on sands and paddle in the sea. My youngest sister next t
o me - she pulled her shoes off and put them under a seat that was on the sands. She was playing about all the day and I noticed she didn't have her shoes and when it was time to go home we had to go and hunt 'em and we found 'em under the seat. I was hav
ing a fever for fear they were lost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any other social activities organised by the Methodist Chapel that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - not really. Only Band of Hope. They didn't have any other - we hadn't any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the Band of Hope organise anything else besides the annual outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh yes. Every - every Whitsuntide - all the Band of Hopes from the villages around they had a demonstration and we walked - it'd be quite three miles - to a what was called the monument and there was 
- competitions for singing and different things and - also for - handicraft work. There were competitions for it. That was every year and of course there was a band and we all marched round and it was about three miles we had to go. That was every Whit Mo
nday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have to pay to belong to the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. Only - if they was getting up anything you pay - you paid a penny a month towards it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, I was in the choir but I - of course I was older then. But I was in the choir. And my - other sister was in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 About how old would you be then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I should think - fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What activities did the choir engage in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - we did - not for a while after I was in the choir we
 didn't do anything only sing at Sundays and for the sermons. But - we did get up the Messiah, but that was in later - it was about 18 - I should be about seventeen. And we got up the Messiah, that was one thing that we did - the choir did. But - nothing 
else really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That's the first bigger venture that it ever did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. See, you only used to learn for the sermons what they called the sermons once each year you see, and we'd sing an anthem or something like that but - there was no other - no other activities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It didn't have any social activities for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. Only once a year. We used to have a tea and a social - the choir did. That was all - only once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the choir itself provide the social entertainment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. Yes. Yes, it was only the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not clubs, no. Only Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was it interested in temperance at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not - no. More than ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 There was no other activity at all organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The Band of Hope and the choir was all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. That was it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was what? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What form did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - he did - he didn't go to any meetings particular but he was at - Lib - he called himself a Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Why do you think he was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I don't know, I'm sure - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh she didn't bother a bit at all. But me father always voted. 'Course there was no votes for women then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The 1918 election was when women first voted wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother vote then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But you don't know what her views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But your father went on voting Liberal all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Some people at that time felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted in different way from their employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well it - their employer didn't bother with that. It didn't make no difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Your father didn't attend political meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no, not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It's unlikely that he'd actually work for a party at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Didn't - no, he didn't do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Your mother wouldn't either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. She wasn't interested at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your father take part in political activity at any time other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Your father for instance - what - how did he spend his leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, you see in the summer - it took him all his time to do the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 gardening
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
. And in the winter he would - well, some nights perhaps go to see me aunts and that or they'd come and they'd have a game of cards played - crib and such things like that. I learned to play crib by watching them pla
y it. Or dominoes or anything like that they'd come and have an hour like. Or perhaps he'd go to their house for an hour you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not really - no. She didn't go to any meetings or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - she would go sometimes - occasionally her and her sisters would go for a dance to the - schools perhaps for two or three hours happen that - in - you know occasionally, but it were only occasionally. Perhaps Christmas time or anything like that.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your father go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
He would do but it wasn't often. You see, if me mother went with her sister like that me father would stop in when we was young you see. So that there was someone in the house with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They never got anybody to sit in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Your father got home from work about four in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, four or half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, sometimes - sometimes all week - 'cos he was tired you see and he didn't - in the winter well in the summer he had the garden to do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he ever attend a club or go to the pub or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He re - he didn't have a club but occasionally he'd go and have a drink at the pub. But it wasn't very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not then - no. But after I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - after we were all left home she would occasionally go then with him but not 'til we was all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he ever attend races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, he has done. Once I remember him going to Chester races - he was treated there by a pal of his and I think he sometimes would have a small bet but it wasn't very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was this when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your father or mother belong to any savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Clubs boots and shoes or for sickness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Funerals or anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
What? When we were young she joined the Co-operative society and the dividend used to pay for the - shoes sometimes and buy the clothes what we got in dividend from the stores - but she wasn't - if they didn't - if we didn't used it then it
 went in the bank you see really. They saved a little that way. But they - not in any other clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you get on with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh we got on all right together especially the young one - the younger one. But the middle one was more hot 
tempered. She - if anything she was always playing up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We had to calm her down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she get involved in rows with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh she would do. And we had to go and rescue her out of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Her quarrels weren't just confined to you and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The what? Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she in fact fall out with you and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 She would occasionally but not for so long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It was more with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Me mother would - if she was a bit sulky she'd make h
er - be different. But she was always seemed to be a bit jealous of me and the younger one but of course we - always we were more alike in temper and we were more to - I will say, to one another than she was ever. She seemed to be more the one out if you 
can understand. She was so short tempered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was there something quite unusual in your family - it doesn't sound as if your mother or father were short tempered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. She seemed to be odd one, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who did you play with apart from your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well the neighbours children just round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, on the back - we'd a - a back yard and a bit of ground there was - not much. We played there or in the street and there wasn't a playground or anything like that to play in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you go to other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  homes to play sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really. Mother never allowed us to go and play other peoples houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But she would let other children come in to play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Occasionally, yes. But there wasn't much room you see in the - in the house then, we had to play outside. Unless it was raining of course.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh hopscotch and skipping and battledore and shuttlecock, whip and top. All sorts of games like that. Ball, you know, rounders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - she didn't like us to get very dirty. We were never allowed to play in the dirt - sit and play in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you get punished if you got dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. We should wash quite quick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were you free to play with anybody you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They didn't discourage you from playing with any particular children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not un - there was only one family I remember and there was alway
s swearing and doing - she wouldn't let us play with them 'cos they language was so bad so we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 hadn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 to play with them. They didn't live quite close but they used to come sometimes down - but we weren't allowed to play with them for the language. And other people were the same with their children - just round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So this one family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Only that I remember that one - yes. Used to swear so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you belong to any youth organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. Not in the village - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you keep pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, we didn't - we didn't keep pets. We all - we only had a cat once and that was all - we never - we never kept pets really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you do anything in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh we had a little - little piece and my father let us each have a little piece of our own and we sowed our own seeds what we liked, in this little bit of garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of things did you grow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I had a few daisy roots and I scattered some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 caraway}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  seeds in and that - and they grew in garden. We used to experiment with bits of things. And these - these caraway - we didn't know they'd grown up but they did and the - looke
d - they grew quite tall and were white flowers on the top and then they went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 caraway}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 seeds. We gathered them and my mother made some seed cake with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So they did come to some used then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. And we was experimenting with them we didn't know they - we didn't think they'd grow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Occasionally, yes, over the fields - what we call - called - could go round. There was - there was about four fields you could go round 
and we say we go over fields for a walk and 'course when buttercups and daisies were out we used to get the flowers you know - when we were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was this you and your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Generally. Sometimes - some of the other children would go. Bu
t we'd just go off for an hour, you know, like that. Me mother wouldn't let us - like us to be gone long for fear we were got lost.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever ride a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. There - there wasn't - bicycles wasn't much about in them days. There wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 bicycles you know. No. There was these - penny-farthing and great big wheel behind. There was several in the village had them and then another one what we called a bone-shaker. There was two wheels and they were wooden }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 wheels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 . They hadn't - other bicycles hadn't come out then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It was adults who rode them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Never any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Only at Queen Victoria's jubilee. In 1887. I ran in the spor
ts a hundred yards and got first prize. And it was one and sixpence, we thought it was great.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you do with your prize money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I think they put it in the bank if I remember. In Post Office savings bank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was this a village sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes, yes. We all - all the children of the village paraded round and there was a band and we went in what they called Riddings Park. It was a private park but it belonged to the Squire, but for the Jubilee he allowed us to go into the field - one of the 
big fields like and there was sports in there for men and women as well. There was one for men - climbing the greasy pole and a prize for it. And another was - cat - these was for adults - catching a pig by it's tail - it was greasy. And that was the priz
e
 if they caught the pig. And for the children there were running sports, you know. Fifty yards and a hundred yards and such as that you know. And we were all given a mug which said Queen Victoria's Jubilee on it 1887 and a mug. And it - it - it lasted all
 - then I think we had fireworks at night in the field - in this park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And this constituted Riddings celebration for the Jubilee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 For the Jubilee - yes, yes. Oh it was a great - we thought it was a great day. All the village was decorated with fl
ags and - and garlands across street because it wasn't a large village and - you see. But I'd never seen it decorated like that before in my life 'til then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother and father take part in any of the sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I - me mother - I think me mo
ther ran in the sports - they bothered her but I don't think she got a prize. I don't remember that she did. But me father didn't - there was dancing as well for them, they - went - there was a band played the dancing and they were dancing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever go to a theatre or a concert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
No, not really. The only theatre as ever I went to - was one as came in the Riddings piece - and it stayed for a few - I think two months about and it was a tent like and you went there and - and they played such things as Maria Martin and the Red \{
ILLEGIBLE\} such as that. But we children only went on the Saturday afternoon - and it was a penny and it - but - they called - played what they called a laughable farce - it were like - dressed up and that. It nothin
g like these theatres. There weren't anything else in village.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever got to a theatre in a place like Nottingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. Well, not - only when we went - my grandmother went to live at Nottingham. And I should be about seven and me father - 
me grandfather, he drove an engine at a lace factory and we used to go to Nottingham then and - at Christmas there was a pantomime and father and mother'd go to with their sisters and that at Nottingham. That was the only time as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You and your sisters went to the pantomime with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 My mother's sister. We didn't as children go. No. We stayed at home. But that was only time they ever went to the pantomime or anything.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, they'd get up a concert with th
e - some of - sometimes, in the village there'd be concerts got up with - with a few people and you'd go to a concert in the schools. There were singing and different things you know of that. Perhaps give a play or something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 Music halls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - was there a music-hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 There wouldn't be a cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, there was nothing like that. No, there wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When we were children we had a penny a week - spending money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 This was every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any extra when you were saving up to go on these trips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, we had to save them pennies up. Unless they gave us - perhaps my mother would give us threepence or sixpence at the time of the tr
ip you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Apart from saving up to go on your trips what else did you spend your penny on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Sweets and different things like that. Only me mother was encouraging us to save money at - in the bank and we had slip from the - from the Post Office 
and you bought a penny stamp and stuck it on. When you got twelve you took it back and they put a shilling in your bank book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So they had saving stamps as early as that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes, that was it. And she encouraged us you see. We'd spend perha
ps on ha'penny in sweets and save the other ha'penny 'til the next week and then buy a penny stamp, put it on these - they were slips like that and there were twelve squares and you put a penny stamp on it. And you take - took that to the Post Office and 
they put a shilling in your bank book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So you wouldn't actually spend very much money on sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. No. Not ha'penny a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever save up to buy presents for your mother or father or your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not really. We hadn't enough money to save up - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It really wasn't the habit in your family to give one another presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Neither relations, friends nor neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. Not - only when she was ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When she was ill who would she call upon to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, her sister. She'd come - she lived in the village and she'd come and - look to us while -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would she come and stay with you or just pop in and out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, she - she'd be there all - and come down to us for - perhaps for half a day and then back again. We only lived very near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In what ways would she help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well if me mother was in bed she'd get a meal }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 ready}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  or she'd get a meal ready 
for us you see. And me father then - he would do the housework at the weekend if she was in bed at the weekend. I've seen him wash the floor, you see, but only when me mother be in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you remember how you got on in the house when your younger sisters were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I think my - I think my mother's younger sister wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  came and - was in the house. And - of course her mother didn't live only about - three miles away. She'd come a bit you see - they didn't think anything of walking three miles them days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So really you had quite a few relatives living near didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, there was two sisters and then my grandmother, you see, two grandmothers not living far away. About three miles each - but they didn't live at the same place. The grandmothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But you had these other relatives in the village as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Your mother's two sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. They got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 and lived in the village you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any of your father's family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 My father's family? Yes, but they didn't - they - they lived in a different direction you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How often did you see the ones who lived near - for instance your mother's sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh - nearly every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would this be at your home or their home or in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh - either of them. Well we went - we called to see 'em - they called to see us it wasn't - no set time we never knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't stand on ceremony?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Well, my 
mother had one or two friends and me father. They called to see us and they'd go to see them on occasion. Only in the - in the village I mean you know. Like calling when they were passing and things like that. Or come and have a game of cards at night or 
something like that, you know, in winter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They would visit one another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 At one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 another\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they see then anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well not really unless they'd meet them in the street you know, anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother and father share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they have any of their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not - I don't remember - no. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And friends were invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Fairly often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would they be offered anything to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - some - occasionally there'd be like my mother ask them to come to tea or like that or if they was call and we'd have a meal or that they would have a meal you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were they invited on particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, occasionally they would be invited, you know. Not - not particular days or anything - just occasionally they'd invite them - from one another and they'd invite us to their home you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would you say that the friends who were invited in were you mother's friends or your father's friends or friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It seemed to be friends of both - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They would call in casually without an invitation as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about neighbours - did they come in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well not real - only unless they was asked really we didn't go in one another's - my mother didn't go in one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 another\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't have the same relationship with the neighbours as with friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were neighbours ever invited into the home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh occasionally yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would they be offered anything to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - if we was having a party my mother would ask the neighbour
 - one of the neighbours - you know, perhaps next door, next door but one - something like that. Didn't invite ever such a lot but she would invite them. Neighbours just there. 'Cos several were invited when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 . You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 People often say that in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well they did. They had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did your parents do when they got together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well they played dominoes or draughts or cards - things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they ever have musical evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well there wasn't many people that had any music of any kind you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Many people divide society into different social classes - in the time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one social class and some belonging to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - yes, really. You see, there was the Squire and those people like that. 'Course in those days we had - when we saw the lady from the Hall we all had to curtsey in the street to her and when we was at school and she came in we
 had to curtsey. See they built the schools. And there were such people as them that - and the managers from the collieries and from the foundries they seemed to be a bit upper class you see. But - the other people seemed more - seemed more on a level. Th
ere were a few that were reprobates as I should say and that but on the whole they was all more or less of one class. Not - not a lot of distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 If you had to give names to these different classes what would you call them? The Squire - who else would come in that category?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 Well the managers from the collieries and their wives - such as them.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about clergy or doctors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, well they would go - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would you say that these were upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes, yes. The doctor - he - and the clergy - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Your own class - what would you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well I should think we'd call it - call it almost a - middle class - ordinary. 'Cos they were poorer than we - they were people that were poorer and I mean - more drunken and such like as that. But that were not - we didn't mix with that lot you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of people belonged to the same class that you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - they worked in the collieries some of them and some worked at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 
foundry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 . And they kept their 
children well dressed and that and didn't - didn't go drinking and boozing and anything like that. They weren't what we'd call the lower class - these that went out boozing and coming home drunk and kicking up rows with the - the - wives and things. We ne
ver associated with that class of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. Well - we naturally - didn't associate with those that were - you see. We were taught to look a bit higher than them you see.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You had to curtsey to the Squire and his Lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 His Lady. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not the employers. Only the Squire. Not the clergy. Not - not any of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have to show respect in some way to people like the employers or the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, you didn't really - didn't take any notice of them you see. When you passed them in the street you didn't have to acknowledge them in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You would just be polite to them when you had to speak to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was there anyone you called Sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Sir? Well we called the Vicar, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You called the Vicar Sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Master or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no one - and the - no we didn't say Master or Madam. And the doctor w
e didn't call him Sir you see we just simply called him Doctor you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever have to address the Squire? Did you ever speak to him or speak to the Lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in such ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Did I ever remember what? Oh yes, yes, I mean the people in the village always seemed to respect us you see. We were thought respectable family you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But not extra specially respected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In the village the Squire would be considered to be the most important person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Shopkeepers? Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 Well they'd associate with you, you see, they were only - the shopkeepers and only been li
ke my mother and father they'd known them from children really.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well we didn't associate like - they come round and visit you but nothing else really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 From School? No, they didn't come round - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The teachers? They seemed to keep to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 their selves}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  chiefly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They didn't associate with clergy for instance or the doctors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not really, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They were out on a limb on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 About farmers? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 
Oh well you - they would come - you could go - you could go to the farm and they'd associate with you, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They weren't - they weren't stand offish or anything like that on the farm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The were working farmers - they weren't gentleman farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, there was only one gentleman farmer and that - was really for the Squire. But they would - even they would chat to you. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the employers - your father's employers for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Wel
l other employers but - my - they would always - if my father met one they'd always recognise you and - and them. You could always speak to them - although they was - owned all the collieries and everything. See, the older ones was more - what you had to 
bow to than the younger ones you know. But they - there - his employers always spoke highly of - my father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you think they associated more freely with him than some of their other employees
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. Yes. 'Course when he got hold - when h
e got hold of one them visited him right - well, right up 'til he died. Yes. And sent him a wreath when he died. Mr Laverick. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he come into contact more with him at his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not - not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh, just ordinary people. The only - I should call ordinary people. And of course the doctors and their wives they went and folk such as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was there a distinction between the church and the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well there seemed to be about the same class went to each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It just depended on their religious conviction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes. Yes. Church or chapel, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What churches did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 There was a Church of England. There was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 Wesleyan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 . There was the Baptist and there was a Methodist and - the - Christian Meeting House. All in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was there a Catholic Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where you lived did all the people in the working class had the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, they was poorer 
- there were some poorer than others in that class. But some of them was caused through drink and some of course they were only labourers and getting a very small wage that the chief that worked in collieries and iron works they got more money than these 
- than these labourers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you describe a family such as worked in the colliery or the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 foundry}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - what their standard of living was like and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, there was one family that he - he was a labourer at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 foundry}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  and I think he only 
got about sixteen shillings a week and he'd three or four children and they were very, very poor. They were - in fact, they were pleased to have anything that you offered them. My mother often gave them bits of food and all - old clothes that we'd worn - 
h
ad done - were too small for us and they were very thankful of them. And one of the - one of the children died and my mother and two more neighbours went round the part of the village collecting tuppences and threepences from different people to bury the 
child - to buy it the coffin and bury it. They hadn't any money at all. They didn't know how they was going to find the money to bury the child. And I also went to the funeral - was one of the - girls to carry the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would you say that your family w
as typical of your particular group or could you think of another family of your group that was different from yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Better - well, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where the man would be earning about the same sort of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Money - yes. No - there - this wa
s - they all seemed to be about the same - they didn't - unless it was any that was spending a lot on drink you see. You all had - seemed to have about the same standard of living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But you knew a family where the man did spend a lot of money on drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh yes, I do. And he - he was getting as much as my father and more really. But he used to call every night in the week and get drink and then come home and then at the weekend he'd call on Friday to pay up for all the drink he'd had the week and ge
t drunk and then come home with probably hardly any money at all and caused right rows with the wife - tip up the table and all - do all sorts of things. And he wouldn't have been like that if it hadn't have been for drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you think that one group would feel superior to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 the rest}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, I think some of them did - them - these that were very poor - they felt - they felt they were superior to them. And looked down on them some of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would you say that some families were thought of as rough and some as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Within the working group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. Some families were very much rougher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you remember whether there was a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I don't remember really mu
ch about that - craftsmen. I don't think there was. You see, there was - at the pits there was all - chiefly butties and men that worked for them and I don't quite know how it was at the time really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But in the colliery they would be pretty much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The same. Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother and father hold the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I think they did. They didn't look down on - on anybody much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class? Was she class conscious at all do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I don't think so - she always - always told us to keep - respectable and such }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 as}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  that you know. We wouldn't associate with anybody that wasn't respectable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But this was on grounds of their behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was it possible at that time for people to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I don't - I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 People who went up in the world or went down in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well there wasn't so very much of that in the village you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 This would probably apply more in a town than a village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You personally can't remember anybody who did go up or go down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really, not in the village, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So you remember anybody being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - the Squire really was - described because he would speak to anyone. His work people and they owned nearly all of the village - houses, most of them belonged to them and all the collieries. But he would speak to his work people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was there anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 Well - the Vicar he would - he would speak to you, you know and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But anybody you would describe as a real a gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, no, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember seeing a policeman in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, one lived only four doors from us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you think about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, we children, we was always afraid of policemen. We were frightened to do anything wrong for fear that - we looked in awe on policemen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your mother ever say I'll call the policeman to you if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, because - he lived so near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How do you think he did treat people really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh I think he treated them very well. If he saw childre
n doing things that were wrong he - he'd stop them you know, and threaten them. I mean - you was afraid of a policeman - you wouldn't do anything wrong if you saw policeman about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The people wouldn't regard him in any way as a bully?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. No, he wasn't - no. No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, he used to come for the rent every fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The landlord himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He was a farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh he was all right as a landlord - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He wasn't particularly generous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Or particularly mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no, he was just ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't have any trouble with him over repairs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, he - they didn't do very much repairs - and painting or anything like that but it - he'd do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well only when it was the strike and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was your father ever ill or out of work because he was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I never remember him being ill really. Not past a day or so like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So really the only difference that was made in the family was when it was the strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. That was the big - took a bit of getting over again you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Your family would never have need to get help from the guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were you given lessons by one of your parents or by a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - I went to a - a woman in the village had a - about - she had about twelve children, I think I'd be about five years old - I went a short time but only a very short time and paid - we paid tuppence a week but we only went in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, chiefly - picture books things - she didn't really learn us anything, not - not in edu - education.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you play about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, in the - in the - in this front ro
om - it was - her front room she used it for us and there was about twelve children. And she would have picture books and read stories out of picture books and things like that. But that was all. I only went for about - twelve weeks, something like that, 
'cos we didn't - benefit really by it. And I couldn't go to - see, I was five years old and couldn't go to a infant school because there wasn't one. They were building one but it wasn't built.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So you were how old when you first went to school properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well I was nearly seven. And infants school had just got built and I went to that one month and then I had to go - 'cos I was seven - to the other school. They would take you in when you were seven you see at the other school. But there'd been none 
for infants. So I - I didn't know much - my alphabet or anything when I went to school at seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 This was what you'd call a junior school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The school that I went to? Well it was - it was the only school. You never went anywhere else, only to that one school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When you first started going to school what time in the morning did you go and what time did you come back in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, we had to be there at nine o'clock in the morning and we came home at twelve dinner time and we had 
to be back again at half past one. And then we was there 'til four o'clock in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So you were there for the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, there, yes. When you were seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Church school. Boys in the bottom and girls at the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 All the time you were at this school you were in a class of girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And the boys were quite separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And it was a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I - about ten minutes - quarter of an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did anybody go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did you have your mid-day meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Home - at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you think of school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh we liked it - I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh they - we liked - I liked the teachers. I loved going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the teachers emphasis certain things as being important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, I think they did as we go farther along but in - in the st
andard one you see the - with not knowing your alphabet or anything you had to start and learn and to learn how to hold a pencil and all that. That it took us a year of that to do that didn't learn very much first year you was in that school you see. Then
 the second year and - and we sat on forms and just had slates and pencils and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 
Then in the second year we sat in desks and - so many times a week we was - we had a copy book and we was learnt to hold a pen and write - like roundloops and pothooks - st
raight strokes you know and that - we did that about twice a week and the rest of the time we had slates and pencils in that class. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
And in the next class we - did have ink and pen all the time you see then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What subjects did you learn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Arithmeti
c, reading - arithmetic and writing. And sewing. Every afternoon we had sewing. To do - there was a sewing mistress came in the afternoon - learnt you how to sew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your teachers concern themselves about manners and tidiness and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes, yes. You had to be tidy and clean and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were they particular about how you sat or how you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, they would. Yes, they were particular like that. And you had to sit up straight - keep your back straight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well she would send you out to the Headmistress. And she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What would the Headmistress do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - sometimes she'd cane them and - oh, and sometimes she'd only lecture them you know. Just depended what they'd done wrong you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of things would you get caned for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - if you hadn't done your sums right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 You\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  get caned would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, if you'd - you would say - they'd give you perhaps four sum
s to do and if you'd only get one right then you'd perhaps get the cane for not getting others right - even though you didn't know how to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And what sort of things would you get lectured about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - not sitting right or talking or anythin
g like that you see. But for doing your work - if you'd - if you'd made blots on your copy book you - you'd get the cane for that - you'd to be careful and not spill a spot on or anything like that. But you couldn't - if you didn't know you - you couldn't
 go to your teacher and ask her how to do anything. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 
They used to then - they'd give a lec - it on the board perhaps - learn you to multiply you know or add up on the board and then you - they'd give you a card with them on and you - you'd got to copy them i
nto your book and add 'em up and if you added 'em up wrong and - that - that was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964  when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964  you'd get the cane.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the girls get the same punishment as boys?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I don't know what they did in the boys school really you see. 'Cos they were different
 altogether - we didn't have anything to do with the boys at all. They learnt different subjects. They learned geography and that - we never learned geography. Nothing like that. Oh, all that we learnt was arithmetic and - later do a bit of composition an
d things like that but we didn't - we paid fourpence a week for the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents show an interest in what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. They did. Used to like to know what we was doing because my father had never been to school and he was s
o anxious that we should have a good schooling as much as ever he could possibly afford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did they find out about what you were doing - did they ask you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they visit the school or speak to the teachers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well my mother she saw them she'd ask them how we were doing and such like as that. But she - they wouldn't go to the school you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the other children in the school come from similar types of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the teachers ever single out some children for different treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In what sort of situation would that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I don't know, sometimes they seemed to - as if they didn't like them you know - and then - they seemed to show favour sometime
s to some children and not to others - I don't know just why it was but they did seem to do sometimes - take a dislike to them and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was this true of all the teachers or one in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh it was - it - well, one - it was one more than anothe
r. She seemed to show a dislike to some of the children somehow. And especially if they were - if they were poorer children. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of a person was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I can hardly tell you. She didn't seem - I didn't think she was very nice and s
omehow I don't think she was suitable for a teacher myself. No I didn't - I - I - shouldn't today think she was suitable at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she teach a particular class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. I think it was standard three she had. But she seemed - she didn't seem to be
 - so agreeable with the other teachers somehow, I don't know. Seemed more of a disagreeable sort of person I should say. But the schoolmistress was very nice. The Headmistress. Very, very nice. We all liked her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have to behave in a particular way if she came into the classroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
No. You see, there was only one - there was only one classroom and the - and the other was a large room you see. There was one very big room and then one classroom. And this very big room was different classes in you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where would the Headmistress be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In the big room and she had a table in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did she actually teach a class herself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not like - no, no, she come and just examined you, you know, a little bit to see how - how they were doin
g I think each one she seemed to do that go from class to class you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How big a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well I couldn't tell you how many children was there because, you see, children - there was more than - that didn't live in the village that came 
to the school - see, and other villages were about two miles away and the children came from there to the school. There was quite a - there was quite a lot you see because we had big classes there may - you'd be about forty or fifty, perhaps sixty childre
n in one class. Wasn't small classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And there would be several groups of forty or fifty in this big room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. And desks you know the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was it a very big room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes, a very big one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't feel overcrowded or anything in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - yes, it was a bit crowded - your desks were a bit crowded together. But it was a very big room because if they had a - dances or a ball it was used for that - for it was a big room. And the - the classroom was a - a big classroom 
and they had classes on either - doors opened like that, you know, to - to shut that off and there was two classes in there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any gangs in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Any what? Well not particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't go about in groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any children who seemed to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well sometimes there would be you know when you be playing games and different things like that in the - in the playground but it wasn't a very large playground you know. Probably just round the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Could you have stayed longer if you could have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, but there wasn't the - you couldn't stay any longer at that school and there wasn't another school to go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't have any opportunity of attending any part time education after you'd finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No, there was no - no - no school or anything like that - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No - I should - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 While you were still at school did you ever have any part time job or earn money in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 There was no part time jobs to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But you didn't do anything regularly like running errands for anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What was your first full time job when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I was at home for a time and then I went to learn dressmaking - my mother sent me to learn dressmaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - they was advertising for a - apprentices and we had to pay thirty shillings to be an apprentice and work twelve months for nothing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Make dresses. You learned to make dres
ses then well, I could machine before I went but - you - they'd learn you to machine and of course the dresses in them days was very much different than they are today. They was all lined through - well you did - did the lining and the material and you le
a
rned to take it you know to keep it together and then pin it together ready for machining. Or course if you could machine you was allowed to machine it. That was for the skirts and - the bodices were all in little pieces you know, not like they are now. T
here were about - should be about seven or - three, two, four, six, eight. There'd be ten pieces at least for the bodices. All cut in pieces and you - you'd have to tack them on lining you see. You did all things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 This was when you were an apprentice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
When I was apprentice - yes. And then it was called scientific dressmaking and - you drew the pattern - like you had a chart - kind of a chart and you drew the pattern on the paper and then - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 pierced}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - put your lining on - pierced it a bit you see and then cut your - cut it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 From half past eight in the morning 'til eight o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was that Monday to Friday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Monday to Friday. And Saturdays we worked from half past eight in the morning
 to dinner time - sometimes to four o'clock to finish the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any holidays at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We weren't paid anything 'till you'd been twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 After you'd finished your apprenticeship what were you paid then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Four shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, it was thought a fair wage at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did it go up at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - not for a long time - I never got more than six shillings a week there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 All of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What was it spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Foods and clothing and something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you get on with the other people you were working with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, right - all right. Very well. With the ones that owned the business I got on very well with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You felt that she treated you well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh I liked it. And I soon learned that sh
e - to learn to drop the patterns and she - she showed me how to do it and I - I used to draught all the patterns - that was while I was apprentice. I - I learnt it quicker than other apprentices somehow - I don't know how it was and she let me do it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you stay on working with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 All the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, 'til I was about eighteen. Seventeen or eighteen. And then I started up on me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In your own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You were working just yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Just myself - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't have anybody working with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
No, we were - she did a bit - she could sew you know, she'd help with the sewing - hand sewing 'cos there's such a lot of hand sewing in dresses them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How much did you earn when you were working on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh I - I could - I should perhaps make three dresses in the week when I was working on my own and - you'd charge about - some - five shillings and some were six, but no more. It was thought a lot - six shillings but -
 you could - you'd have to work very, very hard to make four dresses in a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
When you charged five shillings for the dress was that just for your work or did it include the material - did people provide the material themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 There wasn't any then, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When you were working for this other lady did you feel there were divisions of interest amongst the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - some of them didn't seem to - do - work as I should like 'em, you know, but the - and then if they didn't - she didn't keep them on after they'd had their apprenticeship, see, some of them - they - they seemed as if they wouldn't 
try to do it, you know, somehow, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many of you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And you were all training to be skilled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would you say that your full time job changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What jobs have you done since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, only dress - I've not really done any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You've not been out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Is there anything else you'd like to tell me about your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not really - there's nothing much really about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We go on now to your home life after you left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What was me home life after I left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you continue to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When you started in this full time job was your relationship between you and your parents changed at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. Didn't seem to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was your relationship changed with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, one was at school you see and the other - the one next to me she'd gone to my grandmothers - she wasn't s
o well and she - she was really the - helping there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you spend your Sundays any differently after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No - going to Sunday school - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You still went on going to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And to the Methodist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. Yes, then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You told me earlier of something of how you spent your spare time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And when I was home spare time it took me all my spare time to - I was sewing. I used to sew from getting up to going to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Only at Saturday sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did you go on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I'd perhaps go to my grandmothers or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, if - go - and go down - me mother'd say go down and see your grandmother, see how they're getting on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I should be going on for - I should be seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you make any new friends about this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - it was about
 that time when I - made friends with my husband - he - he - they didn't live at the same part of the village as we did, they lived at - at the other side. And he didn't go to the same place of worship as I did - he went to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 Wesleyans}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  then but where I w
as they was having a - a - a secondhand organ and he came there to play this organ. That was how I got to know him properly. I did know him - I knew his sister and I knew the family but not to talk to really. I knew the sister through going to school you 
see. But that's how I go to know him with coming to the church then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any other special friends about that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, yes. I had one young woman, Liza Brown, she was - we was at great friends and she was in the choir as well. We used
 to go to their house and she'd come to our house sometimes see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would you ever go off together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 On an outing of any king?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, we never done - perhaps Sunday after chapel we'd have a walk round the village perhaps together - that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have to be home by a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, nine o'clock we had - weren't out after nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You had to be home by nine o'clock?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old were you when you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Twenty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you save up before you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, we saved a bit - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your parents help you at all in setting up home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no, no. No. He bought - he - he had a piano before he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - on the hire purchase system and he gave music lessons - helped to pay for it - gave music lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He had a piano on the hire purchase system?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did that operate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
For the hire purchase? Well I - I think he paid it every month I think. Four shillings a week it was. And the man came round for the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was it the man who'd sold him the piano - nowadays the hire purchase is done by a finance company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 It wouldn't be like that I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
No, no. It was the insurance agent - he - I think he knew some piano firm in Nottingham and that - we got it like through him - through knowing him well. You see
, and - that was how it was we got it on the hire purchase - he had it on the hire purchase - only he thought if we could have that and give music lessons it would get paid for and he - he'd have it - whereas you couldn't afford to buy one you see and his
 
parents hadn't a music - hadn't a piano or anything. They'd a little harmonium but he wanted something better you see - pupils didn't want to learn on a harmonium. So that was how it was and it was at his home. And he paid for that - he had it - well, it 
was nearly paid for when we was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 About how long would you say it took to pay for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I think about two years, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well we - we were courting four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you say anything about the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I was the first that got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  from ours and of course they made it like a big do - all our relations and friends come and - neighbours and my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 husband\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  people - they came. 'Course he wasn't - he wasn't born - he 
was born in the cottages so therefore the relations didn't come - there was only his parents and one or two of their friends that came. But it was a big do - it was all held in the house. 'Course we'd moved - we weren't in the same house as we was when I 
first knew my husband - we'd - my mother'd moved into another one a bit bigger. We had a front room in that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How people would you say you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 About thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you get any presents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh a lot. All sorts of presents - all usables. We got a bedstead, blankets, counterpane, chair - oh, everything nearly. And a - a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 tea service}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 - a forty-two tea service and a fifty some - fifty-four I think it was - dinner service and a trinket set, chamber service and a trinket set, two tablecloths, ha
lf a dozen pillow cases, copper kettle, two hearth rugs. Dolly pegs, clothes pegs, all dreg tins and dripping tins. Drinking glasses - six drinking glasses, six wine glasses. Cheese dish, two bread dishes, paste board, rolling pin, bread board, soap dish 
and numerous more things, I can't tell you what we did get. I had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You had pretty well a house full of equipment then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did you live after you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh in a new house - not far from my husbands mothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was that rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many years did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - we should be in there - that house about three years I think and then - then we went in another one where there was a bath room. There was
n't a bathroom in that one but we went in another new one and there was a bathroom to it - a bigger one. That was nearer my mothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Riddings then. And I had - I had two children then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The first you went to - what was the address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Stewart Street, Riddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And then this bigger one with the bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, it was in George Street, Riddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was this a new one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 New - new one yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 A newly built house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. No one else had lived in them before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did the accommodation consist of there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
In the new? Well, we'd three bedrooms and this bathrooms - we'd a bathroom - and front room, living room and scullery. It was quite a big house it was you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Lived - stopped there until I went to Kirkby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 1905.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So you had about three years at Stewart Street and three years at George Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That'd be about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And then you went to Kirkby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
We lived in what was called Cemetery Road. And that was - was a new house. It'd only had one tenant in it. But there wasn't a bathroom to it. But there was three bedrooms, a front room and a living room and a scullery in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - I think we'd be there about five years in that house. And then we moved to - to a bigger house with a - porch, entrance hall and three bedrooms and a bathroom - hot and cold water - it was modern you see, and a d
ifferent range - cooking range. It was a - quite a big house that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 This was a cooking range with a fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That was quite well equipped then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 We rented it of course, it belonged to the Corporation }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We paid six and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 a week rent. Which included the rates. That was considered a big rent really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But you'd have superior accommodation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. And a private - private way to the back and everything. Everything to ourselves it was
. Wasn't a detached house but ours was at the end and it was all, you know, to itself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, I was there 'til I came to Wigan. Let's see. I don't know quite how many - I can't remember quite how many years it was. I sh
ould think it - I don't know - it might have been six years - I can't remember really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old was your husband when you first got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Twenty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What was your husbands job when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He worked in the mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he have any other jobs before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh - yes, before I knew him he worked at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 foundry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - he was what they called a fettler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long was he doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I think - from about leaving - well, not when he - when he left school he went round 
with a paraffin cart and - sell paraffin because there was nothing only paraffin lamps you see in the village. Well then he left there and went to this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 foundry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - I think he'd be about fourteen when he went to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 foundry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old had he been when he left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I think he'd be twelve when he left school. Think he went to the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When he'd done his rounds with the paraffin cart he went to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 foundry}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 At about fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. And he was what they called - fettler - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long did he stay at that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - he'd stay at that - let's see - fourteen and six is twenty-six or seven years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So he only went into the coal mine round about the time you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820142 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was it just before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not long before - about a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long did he stay in the coal mine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - near - 'til we came to Wigan. 'Til 1919 - we came to Wigan in 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he work in the same coal mine all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. When we left - when we left Riddings and went
 to Kirkby it was another coal mine you see. When - when we was at Riddings he worked in the coal mine - not actually getting the coal he wasn't - he was what they called a horn sister and that was to see that the coal came up and down the pit, you see. W
e
ll, he only got twenty-four shillings a week for that and of course I'll tell you - make ends meet as you might say - he took the - give music lessons and bands - music - you know - conducted bands and that you know that's how he - of course it brought us
 in a very good living if you can understand. Well, he played in the band and the band at Kirkby offered him a job if he'd go to Kirkby. And - join their band and he would get seven shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 At the Kirkby colliery they were able to pay him seven shillings a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes. He was a day man. You see he'd never worked at the coal face so he couldn't be what they called a butty but when he'd been there twelve months he was a butty - he had a stall and was a butty and another man joined him and the
y had men working for them - and working for them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 'Course he got quite a lot more money }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 then. But}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  you see it was better there. He'd had to - he used to go at - get to work at six o'clock at this other - when he was at Riddings. When he went to Kirkby they
 didn't start 'til seven in the morning, you see, it was a new colliery altogether and they never worked on Saturdays. So he used to give music lessons on Saturday as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So he had quite a bit in the way of part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 music}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  - yes, music and bands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How do you think he felt about his work - did he like it or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well he liked it - he - he - liked it only he was always afraid for fear his hands got damaged you see with being a pianist and that and his soul art was to be an organist you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He worked in the coal mine until he left Kirkby and came to Wigan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And then he changed his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, here - he was a cinema organist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he do this all the time or did he have any other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, he gave music lessons as well here but - he was still the organist right up 'til he died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You did have children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you give me the dates of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The dates? Well, one is - one was in 1919. Oh no - April, that was your mother's birthday - eighth of April.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Just the years I want.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, well - oh well, just - 1900. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And then the second one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Then next one was 1905.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And the third one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 1913.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were your children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you know what to expect in childbirth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, quite all right. Although I - I had to have chloroform at birth - at the birth of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 For each one?
