\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. I did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you make and mend clothes or did your husband?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh I made - made - made all the clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you buy anything new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, all new 'cos I'd been a dressmaker - I used to make all the things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, we bought the from Co-operative. Used to pay in the Co-operative club then. What c
alled the clothing club and get - buy shoes and things with the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How often did you buy or make }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 new clothes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  and shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When - when they was worn or they'd grown out of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How often would you make a new dress for yourself for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 For myself. Well about perhaps once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How often would your husband have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well he'd perhaps have a new suit once - one year - he'd perhaps - he'd perhaps be two years or three years with one suit, you see. When it began to get shabby he had another. We didn't space any time - when it was shabby he had another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your husband help at all with jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Such as cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh well he'd make the fire but we didn't let it out. We used to keep it in all night, you see, the fire, but if it was out he'd make it. But he didn't do anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, I did that. Pap
ering and whitewashing, painting. But being a new house it didn't want a lot of painting you know, it was grained and varnished inside. So I used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - it - never required any because it was new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you make any improvements to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well not - not inside - no, it never - didn't require any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 As your children grew older did your husband help at all with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not - not really - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he read to them or tell them stories? Or take them out or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I used to take them out when they was little but I didn't read stories to them particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh he had no time for giving music lessons and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any regular household }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 tasks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  for the children to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really. No. Used to get it all done while they were at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What time did the children go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well between seven and eight when they was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were they put to bed by you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well the first t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 o was but the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  one wasn't - Thelma would put that to bed - the baby - but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the children share a bed or a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, they shared a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 All three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - there was - yes, all - yes they would because I had the
 baby - in - in my room. The other two hand one bed you see. 'Til they was older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What room did you use for bathing you had a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We had a bathroom. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How often did the children have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, every week or when they were dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Every week for underclothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And top clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, when they were dirty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where were the meals eaten - which room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - the middle room. We - we'd the front room and the middle room and a scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any occasions when you ate in either of the other rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No. 'Cos it was a large room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Even if you had a large number of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well it was - it was - the biggest room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did you do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In that room. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 On a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
When was? Breakfast? Oh about eight o'clock. My husband eat his before he went you know - half past six to seven 'cos he had to be there at seven you see, had his by himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He got up and got himself off to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So that at breakfast there would be you and the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, sometimes we had bacon then - bacon and eggs sometimes - sometimes we had porridge - different things. Bread and butter sometimes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have anything different on Sundays for instance or on any other special days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not partic - not then, no, we used to generally have bacon and eggs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the mid-day meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What time did you have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well when the children come home from school I'd make a meal then - not a dinner really but - a - sandwiches or anything that we had. As I made - cooked a dinner at - for half past four. Proper dinner, you see, hot meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That was when your husband came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And to eat?-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Tea. Meat and vegetables, pudding always - every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And on Sunday did you reverse the order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, we had it at dinner time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you used to make your own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Cakes and everything. Yes, and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, I didn't make any wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Beer?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I sometimes braw - in the - ginger beer or - something like that in the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you used to concoct any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about bottling fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, I didn't really do anything in that line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you grow your vegetables and fruit or did you buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, we bought them, we'd only a small garden there. Could only just grow a bit of parsley and such things as that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Didn't have any tinned vegetables but we'd have tinned fruit sometime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many times a week did you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And this was fresh meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Fresh meat - most.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you sometimes have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. It'd be cold meat at - you know - if we had it, not any tinned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you get anything extra in the way of meat as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 the result}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  of poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. But when there was a strike on from Blidworth we - the man that turned my husband he boug
ht in a rabbit - they had a - grounds and they could go shooting rabbits and things - that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But that's not poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. No, no poaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you know anybody who did do any poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you yourself ever go short so your husband and children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he need to have larger helpings of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did what? Well he had a bit bigger but not very much - he wasn't a big eater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were the children allowed to talk at meal times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well not really - they - they would talk over the meal but they - more interested in getting food down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Could they choose what they wanted from what was cooked or did you make them have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I used to give them a bit of everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What attitude did you adopt if some of the food was left uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I didn't give them too much so they wouldn't - wouldn't leave any then they'd ask for more. So it wasn't wasted you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 They asked for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. If they wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the wait until the things on the table were offered to them or did they ask for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, they'd ask for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you insist on them holding knives and forks in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And sitting in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. Like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you let them bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not - not over the meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When did they leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, when they'd finished and asked can I let them leave the table or if I saw they'd
 finished I'd tell them you can leave the table you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did all the family present for the meal sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they have regular places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you serve the meat as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I carved the meat as well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What order did you serve them in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I always served my husband first and then the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about when the children were too young to feed themselves - did they sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no, we had a high chair and they sat in - I fed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old were they when they started to come up to the table for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 About two. When they could sit on a chair proper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When your children were young did you feel there was a right way and a wrong way of bringing them up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes. Yes, I though you - you had to bring 'em up - well, the right way to tell them what was good and what was bad. So as they wouldn't do things wrong. And send them to Sunday school and such things, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you and your husband have the same views of bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you discuss them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, not particular but we - we didn't interfere one with the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You agreed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was there anybody that you used to talk to if you were worried about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well only my husband's mother when she'd come up or my mother. Or - or him, I'd talk to him about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How often did you see your mother when your children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - when I lived at Kirkby I 
didn't see - only about once a month perhaps. But my husband's mother used to come up every week. 'Cos she - her husband - he was a railway man you see - he was signalman and she got cheap quarter fare - it didn't cost her much to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you used to ask her about the children as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did what? Oh yes, yes, if she came up - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you tell me some of the things that you felt you ought to do for your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What to do to them - for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In the way of safety or discipline or food. - anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Not - not really. No, I don't know that I did. I should correct them if they was wrong or anything like that you know but - not particular really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about affection for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh - I mean - we loved them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you feel that you wanted them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - not when they was young like that. We didn't seem to have a lot of worries about things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you want them to share their worries with you - I think you misunderstood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes, yes. They'd come and tell you if - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't feel there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 any special}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  precautions you ought to take about their safety for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Their safety? Well - not really you see in them days it wasn't so - as it is lik
e now - the traffic and that wasn't like it is you know. You didn't feel bothered about them like you do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When the children were young did you and your husband both manage to leave them so that you could go out together ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, we only
 left them once with my husband's mother - we never left them with anybody else. Once when we - we went to London and to Aldershot for four days she had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 To Aldershot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And they went to stay with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. She came and fetched them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And that was the only occasion that you went and left them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the odd evening now and then - did that not happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No. You see - Thelma was - I didn't go out so much 'til they were older. 'Course wh
en - when - when Thelma'd be about nine I should think, was when I began to take a bit of interest in things in the village you see. Like such as Co-operative meetings and all things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 There wasn't any other occasion apart from this one occasion when you went away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That you had to ask somebody else to come and look after them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - I - when I went to - you see that's the other - when I went to Oxford I had my cousin came in and looked after the house and the children while I went to the conference you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 This is when you went away on your own isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I'm asking about opportunities for you and your husband to go out together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh - oh we didn't - well, we only went that once away for any length of time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about shorter occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well we - we never went - we took them with us if we went with - if we went out for the day we took them with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 you let}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not unless it was something that concerned them. I didn't allow them to break into conversation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you bring them up to consider was important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - to get their own living - to earn their own living. To study and do every
thing like that to get their own living so that they'd be able to fend for themselves when we were gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about a sense of values in life - did you try to bring them up to consider that certain ways of behaving were important or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - in a way we did. To behave properly you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you tell them that they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any other children that you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not really - no. Not where we lived then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was there at any time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, it was only in my younger day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But not as far as your own children were concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 If your children did something that you disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I should reprimand 'em or give 'em a smack for what they'd done wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You would do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Myself - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of offences would you punish them for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I can hardly say. If they was fighting other children and they shouldn't do or anything 
like that. Doing things like that or - climbing on other peoples property - I'd fetch them off like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Are these the sort of things you would smack them for or reprimand them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I should - it would depend what they'd done - wheth
er they'd get a smack or a reprimand. But I wouldn't allow them to annoy people. Made them to know that - hadn't to do things to other peoples property and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you punish them often or not very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not very often - it wasn't often they were doing things wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your husband ever punish them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not that I ever remember. He wouldn't have let them do anything wrong but he'd - he'd reprimand 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Can you remember any particular occasion when you punished them for something really naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, I don't remember anything particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Would you say that they received the ideas they had about how they should behave from both of you or did either you or your husband play a more important part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I don't know really - don't know what to say quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Which of you do you think had more influence over them about how they should behave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I think me but they would with him I mean - there was as much one as the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Sometimes. Not always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did that depend on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, what day of the week it happened or if we - if we was busy or something like that - if it was - happened to fall on a Saturday we'd happen have a bir
thday and the grandparents'd be coming over and the little uncles and that. And - and occasionally a neighbour's child you know come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Finance never influenced it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your children have presents when it was their birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Sometimes - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 From whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well we'd give 'em things sometimes when it was their birthday or sometimes their grandparents give them little presents you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't make a habit of always giving them presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would they normally have something different to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I should perhaps make them a cake - a fancy cake you see - when it was their birthday and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That would be regardless if they were having a little party or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And they did sometimes have a party and have guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The children? Well, not - I - I only think about once I over remember really. And I invited one or two children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 On other occasions it was relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Relatives more - yes. They didn't make much of birthdays in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you and your husband and children do anything on Christmas day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, before - before Christmas came along my husband and I used to plan what we was going to give them for Christmas and get them t
o put in their stocking. Then of course on the Christmas morning they would be up early and we would say for them to find the things in their stockings you see. The things in their stockings. And then - that was when we stayed at home for Christmas. And w
e
'd have a Christmas dinner and - we had at night - one Christmas my sister's little girl came and she was from Sheffield and she was - she had her stocking hung up just the same with ours and it used to be real fun and we enjoyed it you see. When we had o
ur Christmas at home. But in a general way nearly every Christmas we went to my husband's people for Christmas - they expected us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And you would do the stocking hanging up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 There. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the presents that they used to have for Christmas all fit into the stockings? Were they all small things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - not - not ever such big ones. As they got a little bit older they had more - we bought the boy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 Mecca no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  you know to - things like that. But - they were rather small things that we use
d to buy you know. But quite a number, we used any little thing. Fancy chocolate things and different things like that. We'd be buying them weeks beforehand so we had some ready and all wrapped up separately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You had musical instruments in the home didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, we'd a piano and a cornet. And a violin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who played them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 My husband and the - Thelma played the piano - she learnt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did any of you sing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you make music together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really. I mean, my husband and Thelma played together and that. But I - I didn't - I couldn't play or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did they play duets together on the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Or did one play the piano and one play another instrument?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes - no, they played duets together but my husband sometimes played the piano and the cornet himself - together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Simultaneously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. He'd play the cornet and he'd play the piano as well. Done that may time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you play any games with your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - we did such as dominoes and draughts and we had a board called tumble-in - we played that with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was that a sort of bagatelle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well it was like - it was like a big one - it was about that - a foot wide and about eighte
en inches long and at the bottom there was holes close to the bottom and one and two and three like that holes and the - the tumble - in - was made of aluminium and there was a ball inside it - it was like a - it was long like that and a - ball inside it 
and it made it tipple over and you - you moved the board a little bit like that to get them in these holes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So it was a sort of bagatelle really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In a way. Was called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 tumble}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 -in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about outdoor games - did you ever play outdoor games with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you and your husband play games different from the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not very often. Not very often because he was always music - he hadn't much time you see with giving lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you sometimes play with the children when he would be doing something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have books about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, reading books - and - music books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What newspaper did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We used - the Nottingham Evening News at night and - the Daily Mail in the morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Had a church magazine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Any others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. My husband had the - he took in the Musical Times. But that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did you get these from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Newsagent - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the books - did you belong to a library at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
There wasn't a library - not in Kirkby. We - the books we bought you know like such as Pickwick Papers and things like them you know to read. Three men in a boat and all sorts of things like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You had a book shop in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you read aloud to each other or to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were the children taken out to visit neighbours and friends or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were the children what? Oh yes, if we went - if we went anywhere they'd go with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were they taken anywhere by anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't have any neighbours who would take them out or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you take them shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the children ever go out with their father without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of frequency would this be - how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - not - perhaps once a fortnight, it just depended, you see, whether he was 
busy with music or that - if he'd a bit of time. 'Cos he'd take them down the street with him and - and - like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Like shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did he take them anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well he'd take 'em walk over the forest - what we called over the forest sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did you used to do on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well mostly we to see either his mother or my mother but occasionally we had gone to Nottingham for day - taken the children, gone to Nottingham but we generally went see our relations you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you spend Saturdays at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well going shopping and - that was chiefly the thing. Or a bit of a walk round - round what we used to call Old Forest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Sundays we went to church. My husband played at church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He played the organ at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Organ - church - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You and the children went to the service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. Morning - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 To morning service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the other services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I didn't go to the evening but - Thelma did as she got older but I didn't go to the evening service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well they didn't go to the evening service. They went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 All three of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you and they put on different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And you kept these different clothes on all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes. We'd always different shoes and everything for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you think it was wrong to work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not - not particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Or to play or to enjoy yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I think it didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you allow your children to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well they could play games in the yard and that and - but not on the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What was the church denomination that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So you'd changed from Methodist and he'd changed from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 Wesleyan}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. Oh yes. A long time before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You used to go every Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Nearly every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you or any of the children belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the church run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not that I know of - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did it run any clubs or activities? Or did the choir have any activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not really. All they
 did was in the wintertime - was - they'd get up a concert - I remember the Vicar's wife and the choir together they would get up a concert and give that - in the wintertime. But not others. There was the mothers union that I went to at the - at - that wa
s an organisation - mothers union - I went to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. Well we only had it once a month really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the choir used to have a treat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, they had a trip away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And your husband as organist would be involved with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh yes, yes, he had - he went with 'em and he used to take the choir boys. He took them to Matlock and different places - for - you know, for the day and he was in charge of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did your own children used to go as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well sometimes one of the boys would go but - no, no one else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 At home did you say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were your children taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who taught them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You say that you remember something about another house you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh when we left Stuart Street. We went to the schoolhouse to live and - and clean the school, this was in Riddings, yes. When we left - Thelma was about two and a half years old when we we
nt there and we had - we'd two schools to clean. The boys and the girls school and we lived in the schoolhouse and the schoolmistress, she was there. I had to look after her and do her meals and keep the place clean. We lived rent free and coal and I thin
k we got ten shillings a week. It was paid quarterly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And your husband carried on working in the coal mine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. He worked at the pit at the same time. Then at the weekend we had to make - arrange the school with all - change all the desks and
 make them into little classes for Sunday school because it were a church school and they all had to be made ready for Sunday school - we did that on Saturday. Of course I swept the schools and my - my sister came and helped me to do the sweeping and the 
dusting of the schools each - each day. My husband made the fires. There was a fire in every room in the school. He made the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 fires at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  night and lit them before he went to work. I used to get up at six o'clock in the morning and go into the school and just f
inish the dusting what - because you couldn't finish it at night the dust hadn't settled and leave Thelma in bed - she was always asleep.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How old would she be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Two and a half. And when I came back into the house I got the schoolmistresses 
breakfast ready for - she had her breakfast at half past seven and she went into the school at eight o'clock in the morning for - to give the pupil teachers lessons see that was where they got the lessons and passed for to be teachers before they - I don'
t think they - they'd go to college perhaps I don't know - but that's what she did every morning in the girls school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 From eight o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 At eight o'clock to twenty to nine. And then the - then the children were allowed to go into the school at t
wenty to nine and it was same in the boys school. The schoolmaster there he went at eight - there at eight o'clock and his pupil teachers they were taken to twenty to nine - each one was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you clean that school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, the two 
- there was one on top of the other. The boys was down and the girls was up. And - we had to sweep every room every night of course and dust every desk and everything ready for school in the morning. And on Friday - on Friday night or Saturday - I used to
 
have to mop the staircase for the - in the girls school 'cos it was a staircase up and while we were there they built two - two new classrooms to - and made the school bigger, and two more cloakrooms downstairs as there was only one big room and - and a c
lassroom before but while we were there as I say they built two new classrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well we - we should be there about a year and a half I think to be - near as I can remember. And - we had to scrub the school through twice a
 year. We did that. And - I think we got ten shillings a week, I'm not quite sure, but no more. But of course that helped us along with - for a - it made us - we had more money to play with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And you looked after the schoolmistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes. I h
ad to look after the schoolmistress and get all her meals ready and everything. She had one - one bedroom and one room downstairs and we had two rooms downstairs and two bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And she would have her meals on her won?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 She would? Yes. Yes, yes. You see, the stairs went up between in our house and that. She bought all her own food and I had to }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 cook it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Wasn't there something else that you'd remembered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 I should carry on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I did in the - when the - there was - the ladies was going to have the vote - that was when I began to take an interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What were your views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh that time it would be - was Labour really. Co-operative. You see, I'd began to take an interest in t
he Co-operative Society. About 19 - 1908 I think it would be. The Co-operative - there was two ladies came and visited me and asked me if I would joint the Co-operative }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 Women\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  Guild - they were trying to get one started and I said well I'd ask my husband 
if he would look after the children and I - I would go. And I asked him and he said he would. And I went to the meeting and - they made me secretary of the Co-operative - of this and we started a Guild. Co-operative Women's Guild and - I used to get liter
ature from the Guild and also took the Co-operative News in. And that made me began to take interest in politics, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And what were these views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well they was more for unions - getting unions - for the emp - for the employees of the Co-oper
ative you see - more things like that. And then we had to ask our society whether they'd paid the union rate of wages and different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You started to become interested in politics round about the stage when women were going to get the vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 
1918 that was - yes but before - before 1918 as I say I'd joined the Co-operative Women's Guild and in 1910 I went to the Co-operative Congress for the Women's Guild at Oxford and - 'course there, there was several debates on diff
erent things and it made you begin to take more interest in different things and also in the Co-operative movement and - that what made me begin to take interest in things. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
And then you see the - the 1914 war came along and when that came along - when the 
19 war came along they appointed ladies of different committees and I got on the - I was on the food control committee and also on the Sailors and Soc - and - and - housewives - Soldiers and Sailors Committee for the - and we had the meetings -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You mean Soldiers and Sailors Families Association?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, that's it. And we had a - a meeting every week for the food control - every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How was the food control administered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, the - we used to - they used to send to us all what had 
been delivered - the goods that had been delivered in the village and each shopkeeper had to - had to tell the food control what they'd got but that - that wasn't just at the first. It was when they got really very short of food that they had to tell how 
m
uch they had and if one shopkeeper wouldn't have got rationed for - say for butter and sugar and things - if one shopkeeper had more than the supplies his rationed customers it had - it had to be taken to another cus - another shop that hadn't got suffici
ent, you see. It was like - had to be pooled, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were the goods delivered to the shopkeeper first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes, yes, yes. Yes, yes. And also the butchers had to - divulge to the committee what - for meat they'd got you see 'cos that was rationed as well and that had to be pooled for the different butchers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 It wasn't provided to a butchers and grocers and so on, on a particular basis according to customers in the first place?}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 No, on the customers - well, it - it was - all - well, all - aft
er they'd rationed it, it was but they pooled before - before then they could give their customers what they liked you see and it wasn't fair for the other people.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 After the rationing came in what did the food control do then - were the food controls finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
No, no, no. It - it kept on all - well it was the same routine every week you see, how much things had come in and to see that the shopkeepers would come to us if they hadn't got the things - if they weren't distributed to them properly the
y'd come and make complaints to us and we'd have to see that it was put right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of people served on the food control?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well the - I was the only lady on and I was on really from the Co-operative Society had nominated me to be on it and 
the corporation picked different gentlemen - some off - that sat on the council and different - out of the town - out of the village you see. But there was only me for that - but on the Sailors and Families Association there was two ladies. Another lady b
esides me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of things did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
For them? Well, they - come - those that were in very poor circumstances and their - their husbands were in the forces and we would get them - relief you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where would the relief come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well I - I think it really came from the corp - from the council like, it was council that had - that had the administering of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You voted for the first time in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Which party did you vote for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well it - it'd be the L
abour party really. Because - when they was having the meetings as they do before the election the - one of the candidate - well, it was a Tory candidate - he had voted against the ladies having - in Parliament - having the vote. Of course we felt very ke
en about that and when he came to address us we asked him the reason that he'd voted against the ladies having the vote. And his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 answer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  was - well, he'd nothing against the ladies and he liked them but as the men had always been the rulers and he thought th
ey always should be the rulers that was the only time - that was the reason he voted against us but he hoped we would give him our franchise and I says - never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What did your husband vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, to tell you the truth I never asked him. He voted who he liked. He didn't - we didn't interfere with one another politics at all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Had you no idea what his political leanings were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, I think he was more Tory than Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there just the two parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, just the two, yes. Used to be Liberal and - Tory, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was there not a Liberal candidate round about 1918? Did they not put up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The - the Liberals? Well - the Labour seemed to take their place - there was only the two to vote for - we didn't have three - not then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you or your husband ever feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not from an employer or a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were you actually a member of the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever work for one of the parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you take part in any political activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 He didn't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When you and he were not doing your work how did you spend your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well - I seemed to find plenty of work to do really with - making all our clothes and everything. Cooking - two - the children at the dinner time and then again at - well, my daughter had started to work in a factory so I had to cook her a dinner at dinne
r time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 When she was fourteen and a half. She went to work in the hosiery factory - at Kirkby - there were two hosiery factories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And you had the two younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And they were both at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
 The - the middle boy he was gone to school then - he had an illness when he was about a year and eight months old and caused him to be deaf so he had to go to a special school and he went to the school at Manchester but I had to fight very hard to get hi
m
 to that school. They - they didn't seem to bother - the school authorities at all and I thought it was - he was - nearly seven - and I thought it was time he went to school to learn something so that he'd be able to earn his living and I faced the Notts 
E
ducation Committee for him to go to school. And I got him to the school I wanted and they asked me why I wanted him to go to that school. I said well, I'd been very inquisitive - I'd been round to several of the deaf schools and I said and that is the onl
y
 one that's come up to my expectation. And they said, oh have you. I said yes, and I said that's where I want him to go. And the - the chairman said to me - and do you know that it will cost eight pounds a year more for that boy to go to that school. I sa
i
d, well eight pounds isn't very much for a boy - more for a boys education. He said oh, you don't think eight pounds is much money? I said I don't when a child's education is at stake, and I said, I am his mother and I'm determined that he shall have the 
b
est education its possible for him to have. And they - they - anyway - and I said, and another thing, you say you don't waste money. I said, what about those two night school's that's been a failure at East Kirkby. That wasn't wasted money was it? I said,
 and here you're quibbling for a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 paltry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 eight pounds for my boy's education, I says, I'm fighting for him. They said, oh well the, we'll let you know. That was on the Saturday but on the Monday I had a - and I said another thing, I said, I'll pay twice for 
his education you must understand, I said, and I know where I shall have to pay it - something for him to have to go to this school, I said, and it - if he'd have been right you'd have had to find him a place in East Kirkby where the School's very crowded
, I said, and I'm paying for that through the rates. Anyways they got - I got a letter to say that he could go to that school. But he would never have gone if I hadn't have fought for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So you'd got one child working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And then you'd got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 The other way. Then the little boy's at home you see. He was the baby when Thelma started to work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you and your husband ever get the chance to go out together in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, when - you see, Thelma was nearly fifteen when -
 the boy was only six months old - and she would look after the boy when my husband and I wanted to go out in the evening. But we didn't go out very often because his time was all taken up with the band practices and different bands that he went to and gi
ving music lessons. We hadn't time for going out much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where would you go to on the few occasions you did go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 We'd go perhaps to a friends house. Nowhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What time did your husband get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - between four and half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - well, I think he'd three nights for band practices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Three nights out at band practice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, I think so - Monday, Wednesday and Friday. So there was only - there'd only be, see, Tuesday and Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And he would be giving music lessons then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, perhaps one of them nights the band practice - the choir practice night, you see, at the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did either of you go to any clubs or institutes or pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you belong to any savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Only the Co-operative that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't belong to any sickness }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 scheme}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  or funeral club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no. No. We - I paid a penny a week insurance for the two of the - for the children - that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did either of you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not even walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, we went - no, we didn't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did either of you ever bet on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Ever spend on anything? Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you go to any theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
We'd go to concerts if they was in - in the - the village you see but there wasn't a theatre but they did - there was started a cinema but we never - we never really went to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would there be such a thing as a music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't keep any pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, I didn't then - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any other interests out side the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
No, you see the - the 1914 war came along and then I helped with that for the - we did such a lot for the soldiers you know, we had a - a war depot and we made garments - hundreds of garments things and cut - cut a lot out. I lent 
my machine to - to the hall - we used to go three days a week, different ladies were making all these garments for the soldiers from 1914 to 1918 you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 To the church hall. We had a - the - the Vicar's wife organised a war de
pot and we made everything - nightingales, pyjamas, shirts, everything you could think of for soldiers, slippers. And made - and - and the - they did different bandages - different kinds of bandages we made - many tailed bandages and all - everything you 
could think of for the - for the soldiers. Well that took up a lot of time you see and I used to - the - I would have big bales of different }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8456725\charrsid10772964 flannels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964  and things and - at home and cut the garments out at home - a lot at home beside doing it at the depots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How many afternoons a week did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well, I used to try and go two afternoons a week and you see I got my - a little boy he was you see he was only born in 1913 and - the Vicar's wife - there - her nurse had to look after my boy while I was in 
the war depot. He went in their nursery so that I could go - else I couldn't have gone you see. But with being a dressmaker and able to cut out things they - she wanted me there. That was why I lent my machine and let it stop there so that we could used i
t down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever go out purely to enjoy yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - perhaps a day outing with the mothers union anything like that. Nothing else really - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did anybody outside the home help you look after the house and family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not relations or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What would happen if you were confined to bed - how would you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh well, then I should have someone in the house you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who would you have in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - there was a friends daughter I used to have and she'd come, of course I paid her for coming to look after things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And this was if you were ill at all, not just when the children were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh well - if I was only ill for a couple of days or so they would manage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would you have any relatives living nearby at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Any relatives living nearby? No. No. Only friends. There was no relatives whatever belonged us that lived in Kirkby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But you had friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And where did you see your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Where did I see them? Well - we visit them sometimes and they would visit us, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you and your husband share the same friends or did you each have your own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 Well chiefly they was both}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 But you did have some of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh I did have one friend - like as came a lot that he didn't really bother with, if you can understand. Same as he had a - a friend that'd been a boy going to school with him but - he'd come from the same village and lived at the same village. Those two.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would these people come to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, they would come - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You used to invite your friends to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would this be quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Not often - but - if they was passing they would call you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Call in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes. Whether - yes - whether we didn't ask them or not they would call you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you invite people in for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, occasionally - yes. Or if they called and we were at a meal that would - invite them to have a meal you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you make a habit of inviting people to come for particular days or particular occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No - not - not really - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about neighbours - did you go visiting your neighbours houses or did they come visiting in yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
There was only one neighbour's house as I ever - ever went to and she was older than me and I'd go for advice sometimes to her. But we didn't go in and out one another's houses like - unless we wanted something particular - to know 
something particular you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 People often say that in those days they made their own amusements - what did you do when you get together with friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - sometimes - we'd play perhaps cards occasionally or dominoes, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Games of some sort?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes, games generally. And of course if - we went where there was music they'd have my husband playing the music you know and perhaps have a sing - a song you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would this happen when people came to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Rented - yes. I paid six and nine a week rent for that house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 This is the one that the Co-op owned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That belonged the Co-operative - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 How did you feel about the Co-op as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh, that was quite all right - we had no trouble whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You could get anything done that needed doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Oh yes. They - they'd do anything for - yes. Of course they were new - all the houses were new and they didn't really want a deal but if anything went wrong they would do it at once, you didn't have to - no trouble whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In Kirkby who would you say were considered to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, it seemed to be the Vicar and the Vicar - and the Vicar's wife - they seemed to be t
he most - Vicar of the church. They seemed to be the most important. And the manager of the colliery. They seemed - they seemed people like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 You didn't have a Squire or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh no, no, not at Kirkby - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you come into contact with the important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes. The - the Vicar's wife - I often - you see I came in contact with the Vicar's wife a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the Vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, the Vicar as well - yes. Oh yes, they'd come to our house and that s
ee, we would go to Vicarage and my husband was often asked for supper to the Vicarage at Sunday nights and that. Or I - oh I - they would invite me to tea to the Vicarage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the employers - did you come into contact with the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
The manager's wife - from the colliery - yes. She came to the church and that's how I got to know her there you see and she would talk to me every - anywhere - where I saw her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you have any social contact with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, not really - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the teachers - did you have any contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
The teachers? Of the school. Yes - the headmaster and mistress, I - them, we was often together but we didn't visit one another's houses but we was always very free and sociable wi
th one another. And when we left East Kirkby and came to Wigan they corresponded with us. Yes, yes. The headmaster - school master.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 In general who would you say that these people like the clergy would associate wit with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Would associate with fr
iends? Well - the - the - chiefly the wardens and the choirmaster and such as that or - anyone - shopkeepers anybody but they weren't stand offish at all - they would speak to everybody in the village. And the Vicar's wife she was very, very - good to the
m
. She - at - at Christmastime - all the old people that she knew she would send them five hundred weights of coal for Christmas box. Whether - it didn't matter whether they went to church or not it didn't matter. She really gave away more than she could a
f
ford if you understand but her father was wealthy - she was the only daughter - her father was wealthy and when she was short of money she used to write to him for a cheque. She'd give it all away. Her chil - her child's toys - if - if she was out with th
e nurse and the - and the boy and he'd any toys and another child came up to the - to the pram and wanted this toy she'd say oh give it the little boy. And she'd give the child's toys to the boys or whoever was wanting it. She was very generous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who would the teachers associate with as friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - Mrs - Mrs Garnet and that would seem to associate with more the church people they did. Didn't associate with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the other professional classes like the doctors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - they - they didn't seem to associate so much with the people not as - as the Vicar - Vicar did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What about the farmers - you'd have farmers round wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - there were several but it was about two miles really to the farm. My next 
door neighbour was - her father was a farmer and - they - used to go and fetch the milk from the farm and they would - like the milk people and deliver the milk in the village. And - every - well, two or three times they would go and - have a days shootin
g and shooting rabbits and come back with perhaps fifty or sixty rabbits and sell them to the customers or anybody that wanted to buy one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the farmers themselves associate with the village community at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Didn't seem to do very much - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did the employers associate much in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well not really, you see, no. You see, there was only the colliery. That - that you really know - colliery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of people would be their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - only such as the headmaster
 at the school and - perhaps some of the school teachers - headmistress and - and the Vicar's wife and such as them. There wasn't really what you'd call any gentry in the place - real gentry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Who did the shopkeepers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh well - the
y'd associate with them but - chief of the shopkeepers they were - a bit - been brought up in the village and had turned shopkeepers really a lot of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 So that they knew the village people anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh yes, yes. You didn't - you'd meet them - they'd talk to you anywhere you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 What sort of people would you say went to the church of England and what sort of people would go to the non-conformist churches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, they seemed various - they - equal as you might say. Some of the shopkeepe
rs went to the church, some of them went to the chapels, see there was a Baptist chapel and a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 Wesleyan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 chapel and a Methodist chapel in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was there a Roman Catholic church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No. No Roman - the nearest Roman Catholic that I know of was six miles away - Mansfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
So that the people went to church in the village would you say that a fair cross section of the village community would go to each of the different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes, about the same - yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 Yes, the - master from the gasworks 
and that he went to the - to the Wesleyans and it - you see, they - some of them that we - you would call up - upper class - they went to each place they didn't all go to one.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did all the people in the working class in Kirkby have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Well I think the - the different groups - different standards. Some seemed to be poorer than others - some seemed to have more than others. Dress better and different things like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Why do you think that was - was it according to their income or the size of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Yes, I think it was - yes, yes, sometimes it was their income and sometimes it was because the husbands went to these clubs and publics, you see, made them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Can you describe a family with a better standard of living but within the working class or a family with a poorer standard of living in the workings class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Oh well - well, I will tell you this - the man that worked with my husband - that he - he w
as a - but - they were called butties see and the two of them and they'd two men work for them in the pit. Well that man got the same money as my husband but he drank a lot. Now they seemed very poor and they used to think we was well off. Their children 
t
hought we was well off. And yet they - he had exactly the same money as us but they were never dressed well like my children and she wasn't, and she'd come to me and say that she said her husband said we had friends that gave us money. I said we have noth
ing of the kind. I said }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 it\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 because my husband doesn't drink or anything that makes the difference. And they had a son working in the mine just the same as I had the girl working at the factory. You see that was - made a difference. And they thought we was
 well off. We lived in a much better house - they lived in a poor house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you think one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, I do. Those that gave - went drinking and that - people didn't - others wouldn't mix with them if you can unde
rstand. And there was some of them that - they were poor because they made themselves poor but didn't try to lift themselves up any higher no matter what you'd do they wouldn't - you - they wouldn't come up any higher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were some families thought of as rough and some as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 And would this be because of the drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Drinking - yes, yes. That'd chiefly be it because the mother hadn't the money to deal with them and they wouldn't be dressed as well as other children and they'd get rough and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Were there any other factors responsible that you know of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 That was like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Any other factors apart from the husband drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well, there seemed to be a few in that same street where they lived but of cours
e I didn't really associate with them you see. 'Twas only when this woman would come perhaps up to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 me telling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
 me about different things. She didn't come very often - it was when she I think got fed up and - they'd - the children would say we've got this th
ing and got the other you know and then she'd be fed up and she'd come up. And she'd say - she says - he says you have - you have things given to you - friends. I said we haven't - we've only have what we work for. And they was very poor, they - they live
d in a poor house and everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you remember whether there was a distinction felt between craftsmen and labourers in Kirkby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No, I don't remember that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 
You see, there was - they were - when we went to Kirkby first they built the - engine sh
eds the Midland Railway built the engine sheds and then a lot of people came from Nottingham - railway men and they seemed to be a little bit better class than some of the Kirkby - what I should say, you know the old Kirkby people, they seemed to be - and
 they didn't seem to associate with them, they only seemed to associate with such as me and - and different things like that.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Are these people that you would say are craftsmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Well - engine drivers and - and that. Guards and things like that. 'C
os there - there was only the pit you know, there was no other - and the - and the hosiery factories - there was nothing else not there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Did you ever have a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 No - never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Was your husband ever out of work or ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
No. He was - I only knew him ill once - and that was before the last boy was born but he was only off work for two weeks but he had club money - he paid in a friendly society and the - had club money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 A friendly society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Do you know what it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 Raccabites}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
. And he also paid in the National Deposit - that was a friendly society too and - he got eight shillings out of one and the other I think it was twelve shillings. But I only remember ever being off two weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14646945 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 Then after that you came to Wigan didn't you?
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid14646945 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4391623 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 
Came to Wigan in 1919 after the war. I tried very - the - the first boy - the middle boy. He died. He was away at school and he was - he got kicked in playing football and caused }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5913627\charrsid10772964 p}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414065\charrsid10772964 eritonitis and we had to take him to the Manchester Royal Infirmary and then I - I got him home from there and he never seemed to look up much more and he died in 1919 - July 1919.
\par }}